21635034@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The trust then issues securities -- generally due in five years or less -- that are underwritten by Wall Street brokerage firms and offered to investors.@@@@1@26@@oe@2-2-2013
21635035@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Issues typically come with "credit enhancements," such as a bank letter of credit, and thus have received high credit ratings.@@@@1@20@@oe@2-2-2013
